parts of this project were originally from a personal project involving running modern mpv-windows builds on Windows Vista, which got repurposed and turned into a shim for Windows 8.1 instead. expect weird tooling because of that.

requirements :
- Dependency Explorer
- CFF Explorer
- LLVM-MinGW

instructions for diy :
TODO: incomplete
- open `mpv.exe` in CFF Explorer, make sure to say "no" to loading only 40 MB of the file.
- Go to "Import directory", replace `KERNEL32.dll` and `USER32.dll` to `k32r.dll` and `u32r.dll` respectively
- svae the file